“That was maybe as complete a game that we’ve played this year, and this weekend I thought we were outstanding for 120 minutes. I thought we controlled the play for two complete games. The team obviously responded well from the loss last weekend at BC, which was discouraging, but this group has had a common purpose and it goes deeper than the team, it’s through our whole university. We knew we had a good team this year, we proved a lot of things throughout the year. But we always felt that people were waiting for us to trip and stumble and fall and we kind of did that at BC last weekend, but this weekend we redeemed ourselves. I’m extremely proud of this group, staff, players, administration, this is a first for our program and we didn’t stumble into this, we knocked the door down, and we’re headed to the Frozen Four flying high.” - @gcarvel1993 following tonight’s 4-0 Northeast Regional Final victory over Notre Dame

“It’s happened a number of times this year, where we really played well, and we don’t get on the scoreboard. We call it ‘pounding the rock’, just keep pounding the rock. The difference between this game and last Friday night, was there was a different energy on our bench, we were playing at a better level and consistently getting the puck to the front of the net. There wasn’t any panic, we were playing well, we felt the ice was tilted in our favor, and it really did feel like a matter of time. I’ve said this all year, I can deal with losses if we play to our standard and tonight we were playing to it." - @gcarvel1993 following tonight’s 4-0 NCAA Northeast Regional Semifinal win over Harvard.

"Since the beginning of the season we see that it all starts with our coaching staff giving us that confidence. Coach Carvel and the rest of the coaching staff would always emphasize that this is a special group and we can do some special things. Obviously, last weekend wasn't the result that we wanted but that's something that we learn from, and we turn the page because we have a huge opportunity ahead of us here. We know we have a lot of talent and we've proved it all year long and it's just about going out there and competing. It's about the way we play, it's what we've been focusing on the past couple of months now. It's not so much about the X's and O's. We have to go out there and compete, and the harder-working team wins the game so that's our focus moving forward, and that's what we're going to do tomorrow, so hopefully good things happen." - @marioferraro77 on rebounding from the team’s Hockey East Semifinal loss and 🔑 to success vs. Harvard
#newmass | #flagship🚩

"The first word that comes to mind for me is 'humble.' We're extremely humble to be able to do that for the program. It's an exciting time for us, and it's an exciting time for everyone involved. It's not just the guys in the locker room but everyone involved in the program that gets the opportunity to be back here.
